description: A Qt5-based IM client for the Matrix protocol
contribution_justification: Projects on GitHub by default use issues and pull requests, as encouraged by documentation such as <https://guides.github.com/activities/contributing-to-open-source/>.
contribution_requirements_justification: Contribution criteria are not applied yet.
license_location_justification: Non-trivial license location file in repository: <https://github.com/quotient-im/Quaternion/blob/master/COPYING>.
floss_license_justification: The GPL-3.0 license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
floss_license_osi_justification: The GPL-3.0 license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
documentation_basics_justification: See https://github.com/quotient-im/Quaternion/blob/master/README.md
documentation_interface_justification: Quaternion settings are documented in https://github.com/quotient-im/Quaternion/blob/master/README.md; the user interface is self-explanatory.
repo_public_justification: Repository on GitHub, which provides public git repositories with URLs.
repo_track_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git can track the changes, who made them, and when they were made.
repo_interim_justification: All commits and all branches are available at GitHub.
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_semver_justification: Semantic versioning is less applicable for applications without API; besides, Quaternion is still in active development, therefore every released version breaks some previous conventions. With that said, we might assume semantic versioning once the project codebase stabilizes and internal API gets shape.
release_notes_justification: Release notes are supplied with every release at GitHub; see https://github.com/quotient-im/Quaternion/releases
release_notes_vulns_justification: There were no CVEs; however, vulnerabilities are published along with fixes for them, see e.g. https://github.com/quotient-im/Quaternion/issues/181 and the respective release notes for version 0.0.5: https://github.com/quotient-im/Quaternion/releases/tag/v0.0.5
report_archive_justification: GitHub maintains an archive of closed issues: https://github.com/quotient-im/Quaternion/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aclosed
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: There were no vulnerability reports in the last 6 months.
build_floss_tools_justification: The project uses CMake and there's an option of an entirely free toolchain (e.g. gcc, clang) for building on any platform.
test_invocation_justification: Once the tests are introduced, they will use standard means for invocation.
warnings_justification: Several warning flags are used, including -Wall, -pedantic and others
warnings_fixed_justification: GCC builds are kept free from warnings; Clang warnings are taken care of as well.
warnings_strict_justification: A set of GCC warnings set in CMake together with clang-tidy checks during development are deemed the best reasonable set for the project. See details in https://github.com/quotient-im/Quaternion/blob/master/CMakeLists.txt
know_secure_design_justification: The main developer has gone through the relevant texts and practices the mentioned principles to the best of his understanding.
crypto_floss_justification: There are no immediate dependencies on cryptographic libraries.
delivery_mitm_justification: HTTPS and SSH can be used to download software sources (GitHub).
vulnerabilities_fixed_60_days_justificat: As yet, all known vulnerabilities are fixed and no vulnerabilities have been reported recently.
static_analysis_common_vulnerabilities_j: clang-tidy has rules aimed at secure programming
static_analysis_often_justification: clang-tidy is invoked from inside the IDE so the checks occur as-I-code.
dynamic_analysis_justification: Dynamic analysis is not used so far.
dynamic_analysis_unsafe_justification: Dynamic analysis is not used so far.
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: Runtime assertions are used extensively throughout the code, and are added on a routine basis.
dynamic_analysis_fixed_justification: N/A until we have dynamic analysis.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: Travis CI and AppVeyor CI are used.
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests.
english_justification: The primary language of the project is English.
